FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1776153957
OL,3,CWhat were the five key findings in the
OL,4,CSouthport report?
OL,6,FWhat did the Phase One report conclude?
OL,8,FSir Adrian outlined five fundamental
OL,9,Ffailings in how AR's risk was
OL,10,Funderstood and managed.
OL,12,FThe five, he added, were overlapping -
OL,13,Feach reinforced and exacerbated by the
OL,14,Fothers - which "affected and indeed
OL,15,Finfected all dealings with AR and the
OL,16,Findividual agencies".
OL,18,FWhat are the five fundamental problems?
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/21
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1776153957
OL,3,CWhat were the five key findings in the
OL,4,CSouthport report?
OL,6,FSir Adrian said there was a
OL,7,F"fundamental failure" by those
OL,8,Finvolved to take ownership of the risk
OL,9,Fthat AR posed.
OL,11,FHe listed a number of ways in which it
OL,12,Fmanifested, including "a disturbing
OL,13,Flack of clarity as to who, if anyone,
OL,14,Fwas the lead agency, which persisted
OL,15,Fthrough the Inquiry's hearings."
OL,17,FDuring the inquiry when asked who was
OL,18,Fresponsible for AR's risk, "there was
OL,19,Fno consistent response", with no
OL,20,Fagency "prepared to accept" it had the
OL,21,Flead role, he said.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/21
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1776153957
OL,3,CWhat were the five key findings in the
OL,4,CSouthport report?
OL,6,FThe report listed a number of key
OL,7,Fagencies, including the police,
OL,8,FPrevent, mental health services and
OL,9,Fthe council who each failed in this
OL,10,Frespect, adding it was compounded by
OL,11,Fthe "consequent regular shifting of
OL,12,FAR's case to others".
OL,14,FWhenever concerns were raised about
OL,15,Fhis risk of harm they "lacked an
OL,16,Fappropriate 'destination', with nobody
OL,17,Fdesignated to ensure the risk to the
OL,18,Fpublic was "assessed at speed and - to
OL,19,Fthe extent possible - neutralised."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/21
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1776153957
OL,3,CWhat were the five key findings in the
OL,4,CSouthport report?
OL,6,FSir Adrian said while he accepted all
OL,7,Findividuals involved acted in good
OL,8,Ffaith and with good intentions, "far
OL,9,Ftoo often AR's 'case' was passed from
OL,10,Fone public sector agency to another in
OL,11,Fan inappropriate merry-go-round of
OL,12,Freferrals, assessments, case closures
OL,13,Fand hand offs."
OL,15,F"The frankly depressing - and
OL,16,Ftherefore urgent - matter requiring
OL,17,Fgovernment attention is this failure -
OL,18,Fat an organisation and individual
OL,19,Flevel - to stand up and accept
OL,20,Fresponsibility for managing the risk
OL,21,FAR posed," he said.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/21
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1776153957
OL,3,CWhat were the five key findings in the
OL,4,CSouthport report?
OL,6,FThe report found information sharing,
OL,7,Fand information management, between,
OL,8,Fand within, agencies was "often poor".
OL,10,FRisk information, Sir Adrian said, was
OL,11,F"not adequately shared" between
OL,12,Fagencies, leading to it often being
OL,13,Flost or diluted over time.
OL,15,FAs a consequence "the significance of
OL,16,Fsubsequent events was seriously
OL,17,Funderestimated and opportunities to
OL,18,Fintervene were lost", he added.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/21
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39810
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1776153957
OL,3,CWhat were the five key findings in the
OL,4,CSouthport report?
OL,6,FThe most marked example of the
OL,7,Fconsequences of poor information and
OL,8,Fmanagement sharing, Sir Adrian said,
OL,9,Fwas in March 2022 when AR went missing
OL,10,Ffrom home and was found with a knife
OL,11,Fon a bus, where he admitted to police
OL,12,Fhe wanted to stab someone.
OL,14,F"Had the agencies involved in this
OL,15,Fepisode had a remotely adequate
OL,16,Funderstanding of AR's risk history, AR
OL,17,Fwould have been arrested on this
OL,18,Foccasion and (in all probability) his
OL,19,Fhome would have been searched leading
OL,20,Fto police and other agencies gaining
OL,21,Fcritical information," he said.
OL,26,@vD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/21
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
